This Routine announcements of personnel changes are not WP:RS about a living person needs additional citations for verification. Please help by adding reliable sources. Contentious material about living persons that is unsourced or poorly sourced must be removed immediately, especially if potentially libelous or harmful. (August 2016) (Learn how and when to remove this template message)


Mxolis Donald Mbuyisa Mgojo is a South African businessman and the CEO of Exxaro. He succeeded Sipho Nkosi. Mgojo used to be employed at Eyesizwe Coal. He serves as a director of Tronox and Richards Bay Coal Terminal. He studied at the Wharton School of Business.[1]
